      "name": "awaitingConfirm",
      "outputs": [],
      "type": "gate"
    },
    {
      "config": {
        "promptRef": "system/gen-prompts",
        "subAgents": [
          {
            "description": "Generates a single system prompt for one kernel-next agent stage.",
            "maxTurns": 20,
            "model": "sonnet",
            "name": "prompt-writer",
            "prompt": "You write system prompts for workflow-control kernel-next agent stages. Given a stage specification (name, inputs ports, outputs ports, purpose, budget, whether it invokes run_pipeline), produce a high-quality system prompt in markdown.\n\nRequired structure: role definition (1-2 sentences), Available Inputs section listing each input port with its type and meaning, step-by-step Workflow with action verbs, explicit write_port calls for each output port using literal syntax, and Error Handling section with concrete fallbacks.\n\nCritical rules:\n- 30-80 lines per prompt. Under 30 is too vague, over 80 dilutes attention.\n- Do NOT include a JSON output schema section — writes go through write_port MCP tool calls, which the prompt must show literal examples of.\n- If the stage invokes a sub-pipeline, include explicit run_pipeline instructions with the exact sub-pipeline name and input shape.\n- Use specific roles (\"security auditor scanning OWASP vulnerabilities\") not generic ones (\"AI assistant\").\n- Do not fabricate output ports that are not declared in the stage spec.\n- TEMPORAL ANCHOR (F20, 2026-04-26): if the stage performs research, fact-checking, or claim verification, include in Workflow an explicit instruction: \"Treat the current system date as the report date. Any source claim dated AFTER the report date is a projection/forecast, NOT an established fact — flag it explicitly with a [Projection — dated YYYY-MM-DD] marker. Do NOT fold future-dated events into the deliverable as established facts and do NOT raise confidence on the basis of post-dated sources.\" This rule prevents hallucinated 'recent events' from leaking into research deliverables and corrupting the confidence scoring.\n",
            "tools": [
              "Read",
              "Write"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
